subclause.text:
protecting the civil rights and liberties of children with disabilities who use tracking devices,
			 including their rights under the Fourth Amendment of the Constitution of
			 the United States;

paragraph.text:
the term Indian tribe has the same meaning as in 
                  section 4(e) of the Indian Self-Determination and Education Assistance
			 Act (
                  25 U.S.C. 450b(e)
                );

the term law enforcement agency means an agency of a State, unit of local government, or Indian tribe that is authorized by law or
			 by a government agency to engage in or supervise the prevention,
			 detection, investigation, or prosecution of any violation of criminal law;
